$ SQL Server: create table
@ create table

code {
create table tq84_tab (
  col_1  smalldatetime,
  col_2  tinyint        not null
);
code }


{ Identity columns #mssql-identity-columns

  gh|about-MSSQL|/sql/create/table/identity.sql||

  Compare with Oracle's → development/databases/Oracle/objects/sequences#ora-sequence-auto-increment[auto increment] feature.

}
{ create table … as select … from

  Apparently, SQL Server doesn't allow to create a table from a select statement with the following syntax:
code {
create table tq84_new_table as
select
  *
from
  tq84_old_table
where
  …
code }

Instead, the new table can be created with
code {
select *
  into tq84_new_table
  from tq84_old_table
where
  …
code }

}
{ Temporary tables

  A temporary table is created by prepending its name with a `#`:

code {
create table #tq84 (
  col1 int,
  col2 varchar(10)
);
code }

A *global* temporary table is created by prepending its name with `##`:
code {
create table ##tq85 (
  col1 int,
  col2 varchar(10)
);
code }

}
